223,0,1,0,0,'Exhibition & Tour Ticket','','','','',7,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy a guided tour of the Globe Theatre and visit the Exhibition</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Visit Bankside, the Soho of Elizabethan London, and experience today\'s working theatre. Shakespeare\'s Globe is a faithful reconstruction of the open-air playhouse designed in 1599 where many of Shakespeare\'s plays were performed. <br />Based under the Globe Theatre, our engaging and informative Exhibition explores the life of Shakespeare, the London where he lived, and the theatre for which he wrote. A fascinating guided tour inside the theatre reveals the story of its reconstruction and gives an exciting insight into the working life of the Globe</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ticket information</span></strong><br />Tickets include a 30-minute guided tour of the theatre, plus an all-day ticket to the Exhibition.<br />Once your payment is approved you will receive an <strong>E-Voucher</strong> sent to the e-mail address you provide&nbsp;when placing your order.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Your voucher will be valid for up to six months from the date of purchase. You do not need to book a specific time-slot for your visit.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />Online bookings are for maximum 14 visitors. For group bookings 15 , please contact our group department <a href=\"mailto:exhibition@shakespearesglobe.com\">exhibition@shakespearesglobe.com</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Opening Hours</span><br />October 2010 - 22 April 2011&nbsp;</strong><strong><br /></strong>10 am&nbsp;-&nbsp;5pm<br /><br /><strong>23 April until Early October 2011, during Theatre Season</strong><strong><br /></strong>9 am-12 noon (Exhibition and Globe Theatre tour)<br />12 noo